      "message": "\u003e does this mean that the filter will select any entry which have a namespace?\n\nNo, almost the opposite. It filters entries which are not linked anywhere in the namespace, entries for which \"ns\" (ie. MFF_NAMESPACE) is an empty array.\n\nUsually these entries are skipped over by the \"$unwind\" step in the aggregation pipeline (cf. bson_pipeline_from_filter()).\n\n\u003e preserveNullAndEmptyArrays   boolean   Optional.\n\u003e \n\u003e - If true, if the path is null, missing, or an empty array, $unwind outputs the document.\n\u003e - If false, if path is null, missing, or an empty array, $unwind does not output a document.\n\u003e \n\u003e The default value is false.\n\nref: https://docs.mongodb.com/manual/reference/operator/aggregation/unwind/\n\n-----\n\nAlso, just in case, in MongoDB :\n\n\u003e { \u003cfield\u003e: { $eq: \u003cvalue\u003e } } is equivalent to using the form { field: \u003cvalue\u003e } except when the \u003cvalue\u003e is a regular expression.\n\nref: https://docs.mongodb.com/manual/reference/operator/query/eq/",
